AL-BURAQ Smart Home Automation: Company Policies

1.	Product Warranty Policy
Standard Warranty: All AL-BURAQ Smart Home devices come with a 1-year warranty from the date of purchase. This warranty covers manufacturing defects, malfunctions, and faulty workmanship.
Exclusions: The warranty does not cover damage caused by improper installation, unauthorized modifications, accidents, misuse, or natural disasters (e.g., floods, earthquakes).
Claims Process: To file a warranty claim, customers must provide proof of purchase and a detailed description of the issue. Our support team will assess the claim and, if valid, offer repair, replacement, or a refund.
2.	Customer Support Policy
24/7 Availability: Our customer support team is available 24/7 to assist with any inquiries, troubleshooting, or technical support needs.
Multilingual Support: We provide support in Urdu, English, and regional languages to ensure effective communication.
Response Time: We aim to respond to all inquiries within 24 hours. For urgent issues, our priority support is available to address critical problems immediately.
Remote Assistance: We offer remote troubleshooting services, where our technicians can guide you through resolving issues via video calls or remote access.
3.	Return and Refund Policy
Return Window: Customers may return their devices within 7 days of purchase for a full refund if they are not completely satisfied. The device must be in its original condition and packaging.
Refund Process: Refunds will be processed within 14 business days of receiving the returned product. The refund will be credited to the original payment method used during purchase.
Restocking Fee: A 10% restocking fee may apply for non-defective product returns.
4.	Privacy Policy
Data Protection: AL-BURAQ Smart Home Automation is committed to protecting customer data. We collect only the information necessary to provide our services and never share personal data with third parties without explicit consent.
Usage of Data: Customer data is used for improving device performance, customer support, and product updates. All data is stored securely and managed with strict confidentiality.
Opt-Out: Customers can opt out of non-essential communications (e.g., marketing emails) at any time by updating their preferences on our website or contacting customer support.

5.	Installation and Usage Policy
Professional Installation Recommended: For optimal performance and safety, we recommend professional installation by certified technicians, especially for devices handling high loads (up to 41 amps).
User Responsibility: Customers are responsible for ensuring their home electrical systems are compatible with AL-BURAQ devices. Proper grounding and surge protection are recommended to prevent damage.
Safety Guidelines: Users must follow all safety guidelines provided in the user manual. Misuse or failure to adhere to safety instructions may void the warranty.
6.	Replacement and Repair Policy
No-Hassle Replacements: If a device is found to be defective within the warranty period, we will replace it with a new unit at no additional cost.
Affordable Repairs: For out-of-warranty devices, we offer affordable repair services. Customers will receive a quote before any repair work is undertaken.
Burnout Coverage: Devices damaged due to power surges or electrical fluctuations are not covered under the standard warranty. However, we offer discounted repair or replacement services for such cases.
7.	Environmental Responsibility Policy
Eco-Friendly Materials: AL-BURAQ Smart Home Automation is committed to using eco-friendly materials in our products wherever possible. We strive to reduce our environmental impact throughout the product lifecycle.
Recycling Program: We encourage customers to return old devices to us for recycling. We offer discounts on new purchases for customers who participate in our recycling program.
8.	Ethical Business Practices
Transparency: We maintain transparency in all our dealings, from pricing to customer communication. All policies and terms are clearly communicated to customers.
Customer Satisfaction: Customer satisfaction is our top priority. We are committed to resolving any issues swiftly and to the customer’s satisfaction.
Continuous Improvement: We value customer feedback and use it to continuously improve our products and services.
Conclusion
These policies are designed to protect both our customers and our business, ensuring a trustworthy and reliable relationship. AL-BURAQ Smart Home Automation is committed to providing high-quality products and exceptional customer service. We encourage all customers to read and understand these policies thoroughly. If you have any questions or need further clarification, please don’t hesitate to contact us.
